cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.SY

The paper discusses a security vulnerability in computer systems that can be exploited through network requests, making it relevant to the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact on system integrity and data, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of quality-of-service techniques like Intel CAT falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR), and the evaluation of the attack on different types of systems falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
